node.text:
The C3 Vette I designed only went and won the show!!! 😶

Only now have I been able to mentally digest @ultrace_official this last weekend.

@mapettuning_airridesystem & @spojkarworkshop, I just wanted to say a HUGE congratulations & a massive thank you for trusting & executing the vision flawlessly!
-
-
The 1/1 Vette was so joined by the 1/1 LTO M4 i designed back in 2018 by @goodchubby. Then having not 1, but 2 @lto_livetooffend kitted E30s at the show AND the MK2 Golf I designed,  built by @jeanpierrekraemer at the show in one place!!! No Words.
-
-
Massive thank to you everyone involved, and to everyone that has been a part of this journey so far! @adrian_ultrace, a huge congratulations to you on pulling off yet another insane show. It was an amazing experience! Thank you for always trusting the work we do together also! Excited for next year!!❤
-
-
To all the people I met & friends i caught up with, love ya all! @brianscotto @roncar @brandonkado @vin_tra @players_jay @rotiform_brian @imsoovertheinternet @iambillya @players_rik @adammcpeake @jamespreston_ @cloud_370z @emilkarbc @_midnight_haze @flgntlt_kev @fabs_speed to name a few! Hope you all got home safe!
-
-

node.text:
Too late for a new @lto_livetooffend GT86 bodykit on the market or nah?! 😅💖
(I have a version without the spoiler also, this is V1) CHECK MY STORY FOR A BONUS SHOT!

The High Tech 2010s - I wanted to make this @meguiars post personal, and chose the mighty GT86 as my car for this era, not only because of it's introduction to the car scene in 2012, but also because I recently bought one as my new daily driver! 

The 86 chassis, including the Scion FR-S & Subaru BRZ was udoubtedly brought into the scene as a fun, front engined, rear wheel drive, lightweight driving machine. But the thing I love most is the effect this car had on the tuning car scene. From high end Drift cars to purpose built time attack monsters, this base car proved to be one of the era's perfect bases for a crazy build! I'd done a few old 2D photoshops of them before but never properly designed my own kit for it, so I thought, now would be a great time! 

So I went ahead and designed my own widebody kit, inspired by the original body lines of the car with a slight modernised look based on Toyota's current styling (Supra mixed with a bit of LC500 & LFA). Ya'll know i love a good chunky flowing kit. The car has been presented in a "@meguiars  inspired" colour theme also, with the main body of the car in a similar colour pink to the  Ultimate Snow Foam, tied with the Meguiars Yellow. Cossie inspired roof wing because Y TF NOT. 😂🥰

I hope you all like it! I had a blast making it! @rotiform Six's are a treat as well.

node.text:
Thoughts on the Nissan Z that just made its Debut? Worthy of the Z name or not?

I still wish it was called the 400z, and that we got it here in Europe/UK, but I love it!!
-
-
It has so much, potential but even stock, it's a pretty damn nice looking machine! Designed to rival the Supra & BMW 2 series and such, i reckon it's gonna be a pretty fun machine!

I've been working on my own version of the Prototype version they showed a while back, but didn't get to finish it in time. Will defo jump back to it when I can!
-
-
Beautiful photos shot by the one and only @larry_chen_foto ❤
-

node.text:
What do we think of the new @ford Bronco?! 😍
Why is it so low you ask?
-
-
I felt like creating my own custom  carbon-widebody for it but still keeping it somewhat lifted instead of slamming it but not entirely lifted (hence Air Suspension). Should we at @lto_livetooffend
Make it a real kit? 

I'd love the idea behind this to be that it's on some kind of @air_lift_performance setup, if that's even possible on a rock climbing car? I've seen it on a UTV! Maybe I'll do a purpose built "race" version of "sprint" version in the future and push it further, but It was a fun concept to play around with!
-
-
@blackrhinowheels coming in looking spicy AF! 😍
-

node.text:
Thoughts on the new Lamborghini Countach? Worthy of the name or not?
-
-
In all honesty, I have mixed feelings about it, I feel like it's a missed opportunity to do something super special but I also do like the interpretation in terms of modernisation. They got the main features there and such! But it didn't make me say "yup, that's the one". 

Now, im not a traditional designer or anything on a OEM level or anything like that, this is purely my opinion so don't take it seriously 😂. I think the front end is really quite nice, not that I was expecting something identical to the O.G, but I feel like the rear is somewhat lacking.

It's too much Sian, but I guess I'll be doing my own interpretation for the fun of it like half the internet 😅. Performance wise though, pretty damn cool, I'm just talking purely about the exterior elements. Let me know what you think!!
-
-
Beautiful photos shot by the amazing @philipprupprecht ❤
-
-
